sentences: Ranked #6 on Billboard's Heatseekers Albums in August 2010, the band's music video for the song "Turn Off the Lights" was featured on Yahoo!
The band is now on an indefinite hiatus due to Robert Mawhinney's conviction and imprisonment for fraudulently obtaining four bank loans in October 2013.
The band is now on an indefinite hiatus due to Robert Mawhinney's conviction and imprisonment for fraudulently obtaining four bank loans in October 2013.
On April 13, 2010, Lights Over Paris released its first EP, Turn Off the Lights, on Digital Records/Type One Records.

On May 10, 2011, Lights Over Paris released their second single, "I'm Not a Gangsta", on Digital Records/Type One Records featuring highly-touted rapper, The Game, and was the first  single off their unreleased album.
On August 16, 2011, a remix to the single was released titled "I'm Not a Gangsta (I'm a Gangsta Remix)".
In January 2013, Mawhinney was arrested in Miami and charged with fraudulently obtaining four bank loans and money laundering totaling over $11 million.
Mawhinney pleaded guilty to the charges in October 2013 and was sentenced to seven years in prison.

Another scheduled appearance for the band at the Roxy in Los Angeles had a DJ on stage in place of Mawhinney, who was at his high school reunion that night, and saw the DJ being served with legal papers intended for Mawhinney during the show.
